               <p>(The cloak deposed to by a place that was ripped.)</p>
               <p>PRISONER's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>I have known the prosecutor about eighteen years, she borrowed half a guinea of me, I asked her for it, and she told me she could not pay me, and she gave me the cloak with her own hands, and I went and pawned it for my own half guinea.</p>
               <p>Prosecutrix. I never borrowed half a guinea of that woman in my life.</p>
               <p>
